{"id": "EUVD-2019-8179", "enisaUuid": "e1012191-60e9-3737-9433-1b4642a85825", "description": "A buffer overflow in the fribidi_get_par_embedding_levels_ex() function in lib/fribidi-bidi.c of GNU FriBidi through 1.0.7 allows an attacker to cause a denial of service or possibly execute arbitrary code by delivering crafted text content to a user, when this content is then rendered by an application that uses FriBidi for text layout calculations. Examples include any GNOME or GTK+ based application that uses Pango for text layout, as this internally uses FriBidi for bidirectional text layout. For example, the attacker can construct a crafted text file to be opened in GEdit, or a crafted IRC message to be viewed in HexChat.", "datePublished": "2019-11-13T13:55:35", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T01:54:14", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2019-18397.html", "https://www.debian.org/security/2019/dsa-4561", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:0291", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2019:4361", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2019:4326", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2019-18397.html", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2019-18397.html", "https://github.com/fribidi/fribidi/commit/034c6e9a1d296286305f4cfd1e0072b879f52568", "https://marc.info/?l=oss-security&m=157322128105807&w=2", "https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=944327", "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-18397", "https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce%40lists.fedoraproject.org/message/W5UJRTG32FDNI7T637Q6PZYL3UCRR5HR/", "https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/package-announce%40lists.fedoraproject.org/message/TFS3N6KKXPI6ATDNEUFRSLX7R6BOBNIP/", "https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202003-41"], "aliases": ["CVE-2019-18397"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 0.81, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "12c07482-7e22-3f55-9768-8